&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Courier Health is on a mission to solve one of the biggest and most meaningful opportunities in healthcare: reinvent how people living with chronic and rare diseases are supported.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are building the future of patient engagement for life sciences companies. Our software is leveraged by biopharma companies to support patients in their complex journey from diagnosis to initiating and remaining on therapy to achieve optimal health outcomes.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;In the role of&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;Client Solutions Associate&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;you will support multiple life sciences clients through platform implementation, support, and expansion. You will work directly with our client users to drive adoption, provide strategic guidance, and act as a “voice of the customer” to our internal product team. Your enthusiasm and diligence will cement Courier Health’s reputation as a best-in-class vendor partner.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work in close-knit, collaborative teams to drive impact for Courier Health clients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build strong relationships, trust, and credibility with client software users&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead 1:1 and group user sessions to gather feedback, educate, and ensure client value&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop expert-level knowledge of the Courier Health platform and data model&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive platform growth and evolution as a bridge between our clients and Product &amp;amp; Engineering teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Present business results and platform impact to senior executives at business reviews&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own client priorities and day-to-day project management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with senior stakeholders to build out Courier Health’s Client Solutions function&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2+ years of experience in strategic consulting or client-facing enterprise SaaS&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Team player that thrives working with a diverse set of internal &amp;amp; external stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable presenting to executives and large groups&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analytical mindset with consistent attention to detail&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Independent, ambitious and enjoys taking initiative&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in, or willingness to learn about, rare disease/specialty pharma&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High energy and passion for our mission, our clients, and the success of their patients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;If you are not currently located in NYC, please include in your resume / cover letter that you are willing to relocate.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;100% paid employee health benefit options (including medical, dental, and vision)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;401(k) with employer funded match&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Unlimited Vacation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Commuter Benefits&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Paid parental leave&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Catered lunch on Fridays&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Wellness stipend&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Great Place to Work Certified&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The annual salary range for the target level for this role is&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;$95,000 - $115,000&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;+ equity + benefits, including medical, dental, and vision.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Courier Health is proud to be an Equal Employment Opportunity employer.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We do not discriminate based upon race, religion, color, national origin, gender (including pregnancy, childbirth, or related medical conditions), sexual orientation, gender identity, gender expression, age, status as a protected veteran, status as an individual with a disability, or other appli

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Courier Health is on a mission to solve one of the biggest and most meaningful opportunities in healthcare: reinvent how people living with chronic and rare diseases are supported.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are building the future of patient engagement for life sciences companies. Our software is leveraged by biopharma companies to support patients in their complex journey from diagnosis to initiating and remaining on therapy to achieve optimal health outcomes.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Customer Engineering addresses an exciting range of technical customer needs. This role sits within the Engineering team and interfaces closely with the Client Solutions and Engineering teams. Customer Engineering covers all aspects of the implementation and customer success for our biopharma clients, including product requirements gathering, configuration of data integrations, product support, and workflow maintenance. This role is customer facing and will involve some travel (&amp;lt;10% of time).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner directly with technical stakeholders at the Customer to understand their data and business logic
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define data required to support business use cases in Courier Health platform&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define business logic necessary to apply to data to correctly load into Courier Health platform&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Validate that data in Courier Health matches expectations based on Customer systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with Client Solutions team to build out Customer Standard Operating Procedures in Courier Health Platform as Workflows&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support technical conversations with Customers around things like enabling SSO, setting up API integrations, etc.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to product support and enhance existing support processes, including through troubleshooting and analysis of customer feedback&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ad hoc customer data analysis&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Propose product improvements and actively support the product development pipeline through collaboration with the Product Management and Engineering teams, and assist with functional acceptance testing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who You Are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Skills and Knowledge:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with relational databases and data-driven systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High proficiency in SQL (2+ years)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical and problem-solving skills, including root cause analysis and devising solutions for customer workflows&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Rigorous attention to detail and commitment to quality&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent written and verbal communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working in a Customer-facing role&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong ability to translate end-user functional issues into potential product enhancements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Natural drive to take on challenges independently and to propose and lead improvements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Education and Experience:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, or any general Engineering field (e.g. Industrial Engineering) or equivalent work experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;At least 4 years experience working as a data analyst, customer engineer or other similar role&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bonus Points&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with Javascript&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in the healthcare field, specifically working with healthcare data&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why You&#39;ll Love Working Here&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Courier Health is on a mission to solve one of the biggest and most meaningful opportunities in healthcare: reinvent how people living with chronic and rare diseases are supported.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are building the future of patient engagement for life sciences companies. Our software is leveraged by biopharma companies to support patients in their complex journey from diagnosis to initiating and remaining on therapy to achieve optimal health outcomes.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You&#39;ll join an early and growing data engineering team that&#39;s shaping the foundations of our data platform. We&#39;re investing in a modern transformation layer, reliable pipelines, and richer in-product analytics for our clients and you&#39;ll have real influence over how that gets built.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You&#39;ll be one of the first data engineers on our team. This is hands-on, high-ownership work: building our transformation layer, strengthening our analytics pipelines, and creating the data models that power both internal reporting and the analytics our clients see inside the product.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Build data models:&lt;/strong&gt; develop dbt models and SQL transformations, backed by tests, that turn raw data into reliable datasets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Improve pipeline reliability:&lt;/strong&gt; help monitor our replication and orchestrated pipelines, investigate data issues, and add quality checks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Power reporting:&lt;/strong&gt; build and refine the datasets and dashboards that internal teams and clients rely on.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Learn and grow:&lt;/strong&gt; work closely with senior engineers, take part in code review, and steadily take on more ownership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who You Are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;We&#39;re open on exact tools — we care about fundamentals and trajectory. You&#39;ll likely have most of the following:&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3-5 years of professional data engineering experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strong SQL:&lt;/strong&gt; you write correct, readable SQL and understand relational data modeling&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Data experience:&lt;/strong&gt; you&#39;ve developed data pipelines and transformations in production environments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Eagerness to learn:&lt;/strong&gt; you take feedback well, ask good questions, and are excited to grow as a data engineer&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Nice to have: exposure to dbt, CDC / replication or orchestration tools (e.g. Estuary Flow, Debezium/Kafka, Airflow), a cloud data warehouse (ex. Redshift), a BI tool (ex. Sigma, Looker); comfort with PostgreSQL or a similar database.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Our stack&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Databases:&lt;/strong&gt; PostgreSQL across our production and analytics environments, with room to grow into a cloud warehouse (ex. Redshift) as we scale&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ingestion:&lt;/strong&gt; CDC / streaming replication into analytics (evaluating tools like Estuary Flow and Debezium/Kafka)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Transformation:&lt;/strong&gt; building out a version-controlled, dbt-based staging/marts layer with data tests and CI/CD&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Orchestration:&lt;/strong&gt; scheduled, observable pipeline runs (e.g. Airflow or similar)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;BI &amp;amp; embedded analytics:&lt;/strong&gt; a modern BI and embedding platform (we use Sigma) for internal reporting and in-product client analytics, with a maturing semantic/metrics layer&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Courier Health is on a mission to solve one of the biggest and most meaningful opportunities in healthcare: reinvent how people living with chronic and rare diseases are supported.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are building the future of patient engagement for life sciences companies. Our software is leveraged by biopharma companies to support patients in their complex journey from diagnosis to initiating and remaining on therapy to achieve optimal health outcomes.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Courier Health is on a mission to solve one of the biggest and most meaningful opportunities in healthcare: reinvent how people living with chronic and rare diseases are supported.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are building the future of patient engagement for life sciences companies. Our software is leveraged by biopharma companies to support patients in their complex journey from diagnosis to initiating and remaining on therapy to achieve optimal health outcomes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Come Build with Us&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is based out of our New York City office. We are an office-first company that values in-person collaboration four days per week, while also providing flexibility as needed. If you are curious, resourceful, and genuinely excited to help build a world-class team, we would love to meet you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;The Opportunity&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Courier Health is at an inflection point. We exist to get patients faster, better access to life-saving therapies, and the relationships we build with our life sciences clients are how that happens. Our clients are biopharma companies running complex patient support programs, and our Client Solutions team is the partner those clients rely on when it matters.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As Director of Client Solutions, you will own a dedicated portfolio of accounts and manage the team built to serve them. You are accountable for both as an integrated unit: setting the standard for how the team shows up, driving retention and growth across the book of business, and personally serving as the senior strategic partner for a set of our most important enterprise accounts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a role for someone who wants to do consequential work and build the function that delivers it. You&#39;ll have real influence over how Courier Health serves its clients, how the Client Solutions practice scales, and ultimately, how many patients get the support they need.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What You&#39;ll Build&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strategic ownership of flagship accounts.&lt;/strong&gt; You will personally serve as the senior partner for a set of our most important clients. As a critical thought partner, you will advise VP and C-suite level stakeholders on their Patient Services and Field Access strategy. You are comfortable operating at the executive level and equally comfortable rolling up your sleeves to support specific workstreams and deliverables when the moment calls for it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A high-performing Client Solutions team.&lt;/strong&gt; You will lead, coach, and grow a team of Engagement Managers and Client Solution Associates. You set clear expectations, raise the bar on client work, and help each person sharpen their strategic instincts. You set the standard and coach the team to own it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A portfolio that hits its goals.&lt;/strong&gt; You own the long-term health of a book of business: retention, renewals, and expansion across your team’s accounts. You know where every relationship stands, where the risks are, and what the upside is, and you will partner with our commercial team to pursue it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A smarter way to scale.&lt;/strong&gt; You will build and define repeatable frameworks, processes, and best practices that let us deliver consistently as we scale. Your job is to find the right structures that create consistency without slowing things d

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Courier Health is on a mission to solve one of the biggest and most meaningful opportunities in healthcare: reinvent how people living with chronic and rare diseases are supported.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are building the future of patient engagement for life sciences companies. Our software is leveraged by biopharma companies to support patients in their complex journey from diagnosis to initiating and remaining on therapy to achieve optimal health outcomes.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Courier Health has a strong product, a growing customer base, and a market that is increasingly ready to buy. As Director of Growth Marketing, you will drive demand generation, marketing operations, and events, support the programs, infrastructure, and team that turn market interest into qualified opportunities and qualified opportunities into evangelical customers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own Courier Health’s demand generation strategy and execution across channels, including paid, organic, email, events, content syndication, etc.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own Courier Health’s events program, including industry conferences and our annual Patient Innovators Summit.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop a field marketing strategy that supports pipeline generation and acceleration in priority accounts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help develop, run and iterate upon account-based marketing programs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Refine and maintain the attribution model and reporting infrastructure that connects marketing activity to pipeline and revenue.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Refine lead scoring, routing, Marketing-to-Sales handoffs, and SLA frameworks in partnership with Sales.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay at the cutting-edge of B2B demand gen, helping to foster a culture of experimentation &amp;amp; testing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;AI-native — you use tools that make your programs smarter and faster.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who You Are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;8+ years of growth or demand generation marketing experience in B2B SaaS; enterprise software or regulated industry experience strongly preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated track record building and scaling demand gen programs that produce measurable pipeline.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience owning or co-owning an events program, including at least one owned/produced event.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong marketing operations chops: you understand the stack, you can build the attribution model, and you can run the analysis yourself.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep ABM experience: account tiering, personalized program design, and multi-channel orchestration.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;People manager with a track record of developing strong individual contributors.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experimentation mindset: you are energized by testing and rigorous about learning.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong communicator who can present strategy and results to senior leadership clearly and confidently.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;100% paid employee health benefit options (including medical, dental, and vision)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;401(k) with employer funded match&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Unlimited Vacation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Commuter Benefits&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Paid parental leave&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Catered lunch on Fridays&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Wellness stipend&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The annual salary range for the target level for this role is $160,000 - $200,000 + equity + benefits, including medical, dental, and vision. Final compensation will be determined based on a variety of factors including relevant experience, interview performance, and internal equity.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Courier Heal

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Courier Health is on a mission to solve one of the biggest and most meaningful opportunities in healthcare: reinvent how people living with chronic and rare diseases are supported.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are building the future of patient engagement for life sciences companies. Our software is leveraged by biopharma companies to support patients in their complex journey from diagnosis to initiating and remaining on therapy to achieve optimal health outcomes.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Come Build with Us&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Courier Health is a New York City-based technology company on a mission to improve the patient experience for hundreds of millions of people living with a chronic condition or rare disease. The company develops and delivers the fastest-growing patient experience solution for the life sciences industry.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Companies that choose Courier Health are achieving double-digit improvements to patient starts, time-to-start and ongoing adherence to life-altering therapies. As host of the invite-only Patient Innovators Summit and publisher of &lt;em&gt;The State of Patient-Centricity in Biopharma&lt;/em&gt; report, Courier Health is backed by leading investors, including Oak HC/FT, Norwest and Work-Bench.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;notion-enable-hover&quot; data-token-index=&quot;0&quot;&gt;This role is based out of our New York City Office. We’re an office-first company that values in-person collaboration 4 days per week, while also providing flexibility as needed. If you’re scrappy, resourceful, and excited to help build a world-class team we’d love to meet you!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;The Opportunity&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As Director of Legal, you will be Courier Health&#39;s first dedicated legal hire, reporting directly to the CFO. You will build the legal infrastructure that lets a high-growth Series B company operate smoothly and serve as a trusted strategic resource for leadership.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;What You&#39;ll Build&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Legal infrastructure that scales.&lt;/strong&gt; Evaluate, strengthen, and expand the frameworks, templates, and processes that let Courier Health manage its legal affairs without slowing down. From commercial agreements to data processing addenda, you would ensure that the right structures exist and that they&#39;re adopted by teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cross-functional partnership.&lt;/strong&gt; Partnering across the organization to help navigate key decisions. You will be asked to be present, practical and decisive, setting up legal to be an accelerant, not a bottleneck, to decision-making.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strategic risk judgment.&lt;/strong&gt; Serve as a sounding board for the CFO and executive team on legal risk across the business. Flag what matters, contextualize what doesn&#39;t, and help leadership make confident decisions with the information they need.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Rigorous oversight of compliance and regulatory risk.&lt;/strong&gt; Courier Health handles sensitive patient data on behalf of the world&#39;s leading biopharma companies, and we take that responsibility seriously. You will be accountable for ensuring the right legal and compliance frameworks are in place, working closely with specialized outside counsel on HIPAA and data privacy matters, and ensuring that nothing falls through the cracks.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Legal process that runs at scale.&lt;/strong&gt; Design how legal work flows at Courier Health: intake, triage, turnaround expectations, and escalation paths. Build systems that keep legal proactive, and not reactive.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;What Makes You Successful&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;8–12+ years of legal experience, ideally including meaningful time in-house at a technology or healthcare technology company&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;J.D. from an accredited law school; licens

